Messaging

Please note: All message replies MUST follow the format specified, even if there are errors. Error messages must be padded / cropped to the expected length.

This prevents attackers from knowing what messages are being sent by analysing the encrypted message responses.

Furthermore, we always reply with an integrity checksum which is a simple sha256 hash of the entire decrypted message, which proves to the sender that the message arrived exactly as it was sent and enables the sender to track its messages both with a handle and integrity checksum.

Encryption Layers

All communications with Stronghold require the use of a sessionKey using well known asymmetric crypto, except the first key exchange. Furthermore, a second layer of encryption can be applied with "one-time-keys" that are transient and serve for encrypting one message exchange. Without passing a sessName, null responses will be returned.

Phoning Home

In cases where Stronghold encounters an error, such as a request for a seed that does not exist or is encrypted with a key it does not know, it should notify the supervisor that an error occurred. As mentioned above in "Messaging", it should still attempt to send a well-formed reply to the caller.
